news.title: Hyderabad: HYDRAA reclaims encroached government land worth ₹15,000 crore
news.para: Hyderabad's HYDRAA reclaimed over 300 acres of government land in Gajularamaram, valued at approximately Rs 15,000 crore, after identifying encroachments by politicians, real estate players, and bureaucrats. The operation, initiated following public complaints, involved clearing illegal structures while sparing homes of poor families. Authorities are filing complaints against individuals involved in fraudulent land deals and fake documentation.

news.title: Gurugram: 350 shanties, illegal building razed in colony along Golf Course Road
news.para: In Saraswati Kunj, Gurugram, authorities demolished around 350 shanties and other illegal structures to restore road access along Golf Course Road. The DTCP's action aims to prevent further unauthorized occupation in the area, which has been plagued by disputes and illegal construction since 2004. This crackdown follows previous demolitions of houses built in violation of approved plans.

news.title: Kerala CM to inaugurate RAY flats in Fort Kochi on September 27
news.para: Chief Minister Pinarayi Vijayan will inaugurate the Rajiv Awas Yojana housing complexes in Fort Kochi on September 27, benefiting 394 families from Mattancherry slums. The project features two complexes with hundreds of residential units, built by the city corporation and Cochin Smart Mission Ltd.

news.title: Amid misleading ads by builders, government asks states, RERAs to take action
news.para: The Centre has directed states and RERAs to curb misleading advertisements by builders using government-style terminology, aiming to protect homebuyers from deception. This action follows discussions at a RERA Central Advisory Council meeting, where concerns were raised about undisclosed publishers and promoters bypassing mandatory disclosure norms. The ministry is urging states to submit reports and address data mismatches across platforms.

news.title: Mumbai: Economics Offences Wing files chargsheet against builder for ₹13 crore fraud
news.para: Lalit Jain faces charges for allegedly defrauding a Nagpur businessman of ₹12.50 crore in a South Mumbai redevelopment project by concealing property litigation and failing to deliver promised equity and returns.

news.title: Enforcement directorate searches premises linked to Imperial Group in Himachal, Delhi
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) in Shimla has conducted searches at six locations in Himachal Pradesh and Delhi, targeting the Imperial Group and its chairman, Manavinder Singh, along with his wife and associates. This action, under FEMA, 1999, is in response to allegations of undisclosed foreign assets and investments exceeding Rs 80 crore.

news.title: Scrap OCs of housing societies, industrial units not conserving water: Gurugram MP
news.para: Gurgaon MP Rao Inderjit Singh expressed concerns over widespread violation of water conservation rules in residential and industrial units, despite existing laws. He emphasized that water conservation measures are only implemented on paper to obtain occupancy certificates (OC) and are later neglected.

news.title: Noida Airport set to begin operations post-Diwali; foreign airlines in talks for flight services
news.para: Noida International Airport (NIA) in Jewar is set to commence operations by the end of this year, with the inauguration planned for October 30 and flight operations starting within 45 days. The airport's Phase 1 is nearing completion, featuring a runway, passenger terminal, and cargo terminal, with IndiGo and Akasa Air confirmed as launch carriers.

news.title: Crackdown on developers in five illegal colonies of Ludhiana
news.para: Ludhiana's municipal commissioner, Aaditya Dachalwal, initiated a crackdown on illegal colonies in Shimlapuri, Jaspal Bangar, and Kanganwal, ordering demolitions, sealing drives, and police cases against developers. Dachalwal also warned his own inspectors of disciplinary action for failing to prevent illegal construction. The crackdown includes halting property registrations and sealing or demolishing illegal structures in multiple colonies.

news.title: Goa: Chimbel residents oppose Unity Mall, say it is threat to lake
news.para: Chimbel villagers are protesting the Unity Mall project after the SEIAA issued an environmental clearance, fearing threats to the local lake and aquifers. Concerns over environmental impact, livelihoods, and hydrogeology have resurfaced, reminiscent of the opposed IT Park project. Locals, supported by the panchayat, cite lack of transparency and plan a rally against the mall and a government proposal.

news.title: Maharashtra may soon get independent authority to oversee redevelopment projects
news.para: Maharashtra's housing department is nearing a decision on establishing an independent authority, mirroring MahaRERA, to oversee redevelopment projects. This move addresses the growing demand for a transparent and accountable framework, fueled by increasing redevelopment initiatives. The proposed authority aims to standardize processes, resolve disputes, and ensure financial facilitation, ultimately protecting the interests of housing society members.

news.title: Builders await clarity on GST benefits to homebuyers
news.para: Consumers anticipate GST rate reductions across various sectors, but homebuyers might experience delays in reaping the benefits. Real estate industry leaders express uncertainty regarding cement manufacturers passing on the reduced rates. Cost reductions will primarily benefit projects in the early construction phases, with potential impacts expected in October.

news.title: Bombay HC directs Maharashtra govt to address understaffing in SRA & take action against illegalities
news.para: The Bombay High Court is concerned about the Slum Rehabilitation Authority's (SRA) understaffing. It directs the state government to address the issue. The court highlights rampant illegal property transfers within SRA projects. A case involving a disputed allotment letter is examined. The court questions the occupation of a building without a certificate for 15 years.

news.title: Uttarakhand HC upholds RERA order against Paratus Real Estates
news.para: The Uttarakhand High Court has supported a RERA order, instructing Paratus Real Estates to deposit 50% of the penalty before their appeal. This decision rejected the promoter's argument for a 30% deposit under the RERA Act. The court emphasized the Act's purpose to protect consumer interests in real estate, advocating for its strict interpretation.

news.title: Lodha Developers sells 24-acre land in Mumbai to STT Global Data Centres for ₹500 crore
news.para: Lodha Developers has sold over 24 acres of land in the Mumbai region to STT Global Data Centres for approximately Rs 500 crore, with the land deal already registered. This transaction follows Lodha's MoU with the Maharashtra government to establish a green integrated data centre park at Palava, projecting a Rs 30,000 crore investment and creating 6,000 jobs.

news.title: Government to fast track land ownership rights for Bengali families in Gadchiroli, Nagpur
news.para: Revenue Minister Chandrashekhar Bawankule announced the fast-tracking of land ownership rights for nearly 40,000 Bengali families in Gadchiroli, descendants of those who fled East Pakistan. The district collector has been directed to prioritize the proposal for ownership transfer, pending for decades. Drones will be used for land survey mapping, and private workers will be hired to expedite land measurement.

news.title: Illegal colony razed in Ludhiana’s Mundian Kalan area
news.para: The Ludhiana municipal corporation, following commissioner Aaditya Dachalwal's directives, demolished an illegal colony in Mundian Kalan, targeting the developer and structures. This action is part of an ongoing campaign against unauthorized construction across the city.

news.title: Surat: SUDA, JICA officials review model town planning schemes
news.para: Surat Urban Development Authority (SUDA) and JICA officials convened to assess model town planning schemes for the bullet train station area, with five schemes developed incorporating advanced urban planning concepts. TP schemes 61 and 63 have received draft approval, while scheme 61 is submitted as a Preliminary Town Planning Scheme.

news.title: Registrars may get power to verify land records before deals
news.para: The Centre's upcoming Registration Bill empowers states to establish regulations for registrars to meticulously verify land rights records, aiming to combat fraud and minimize legal disputes in property transactions. This initiative seeks to provide enhanced security for buyers and investors through thorough due diligence. The bill also promotes paperless registration and transparency, replacing the outdated 1908 Registration Act.

news.title: Allottee fails to pay auction quote price, loses Mysuru site
news.para: Mysuru Development Authority cancelled the allotment of a prime plot after the winning bidder failed to complete payment formalities despite quoting a staggering Rs 2 crore, far exceeding the base price. Simultaneously, another commercial plot sale progresses with a bidder paying 25% of their Rs 8.6 crore bid.
